Yosai became the Separatist Leader of Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus which was reestablished on 15th October 1983. After the presidential election his party started to make the premature development plans on the North part of Cyprus. Most of the Green area of Northern Cyprus turned to Yellow. Thanks to C.P.R.A. unions and individuals who are working for the green movement, Northern Cyprus is still protected by the old Green line border.

The years 2007 and 2008 was the most serious years of the green movement in Northern Cyprus. Within short period of time several activists from young age to older age were arrested and jailed. Many cases came to the courts and many of the activists were jailed from days to more than 1 year. Members of The R.O.S.E. (Roche Arakanais Social et Educative) Association were subject to threats from the North side and as a result, the AGREFRA case was opened after it was reported to the police. In April 2008 a team including the AGRAFRA delegate and the ICTA
coordinator carried out a survey of the area with European and Turkish police officers.
